<br>
Leveling an Enchanter can be fun because the class thrives in dungeon or other high mob density environments.  Though it's often hard to find groups willing to dungeon crawl before Seb (depends on your server's population).  Solo'ing is much more adventuresome (and rewarding) as an Enchanter versus a SK, though there's a much higher risk factor involved.<br>
<br>
If all you do is Vox/Naggy, you won't be mez'ing anything really on raids anyway.<br>
<br>
If you've got a lot of 65 characters, but hate leveling, the most enjoyable time you'll have is probably to unpack one of those and get some of the more fun AA's or join a raiding guild more suited to your style.<br>
<br>
